title: Mother West Wind 'Why' Stories
creator: Thornton W. Burgess
description: LibriVox recording of Mother West Wind 'Why' Stories, by Thornton W. Burgess. Thornton W. Burgess was a conservationist and prolific author of children's books. His gently humorous stories about the animals of the meadows and woods teach little lessons about getting along with others; they are perfect bedtime stories for small children. (Summary by Laurie Anne Walden) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. Download M4B (77MB) For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
subject: Children; nature; animals; Librivox; audiobook
